CatDescriptText: Miss Grey Dugger, 144 Julius Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1957, pg.3 with question: "Do you think Pennsylvania's 'blue laws' against 'unnecessary' Sunday sales should be enforced?" answer reads: "I don't think that they should be enforced. A lot of people just don't have time during the week to shop."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Grey Dugger, wearing light colored head scarf and corduroy coat with single button, standing in front of light colored marble pillar between store windows, one on left with shoes, and one on right with lamps
